INSTALLATION:
-------------
Simply drag the drawer BCS in the place where you wish to have it.
That's all! BCS will automatically recognize the right path to access the
necessary files.

SYSTEM REQUIRED:  An AMIGA (surprised?) with a minimum of 1 Mb RAM.
----------------

GOAL OF THE GAME:
-----------------

Creating a "Bonhomme" as shown in the left part of the screen, in the right
part with the help of six buttons.

When you achieve it, a champion cup will appear!
To continue, just click on the button <CREATION>.
There is some help available with the pull down menus and some options that
I let you discover...

This game was primarily intended for kids aged 3-4 but I added a little
module to measure the memory of everyone that wish to compete! It is called
<BILAN> and last on 7 "bonhommes" before giving a result. For the moment
everything is written in french. Sorry... If I see enough interrest, I will
be happy to make an English version of BCS or every other language that is
asked for (with a good dictionnary and a little help!)


FUNCTIONS :
-----------
BCS is surely enough simple that it is not worth describing it! Just try...

Some points must be specified:

1/ When starting, BCS will load as much "Bonhommes" as possible depending
   on the available free memory at that moment. To do so, click anywhere
   on the presentation screen...
2/ Running BCS should not alterate the multitasking.
3/ When you quit BCS, choose the right option depending on what you wish to
   do: "Quitter + Vider RAM" will quit and free the RAM used by the
   "Bonhommes" otherwise, the directory will remains. This choice is
   historical: It was used during the debugging phase and I found it
   convenient for adding in live, some new "Bonhommes"...
4/ The <CREATION> button remains disabled as long as the right "Bonhomme"
   hasn't been found.
5/ The 6 finding buttons become disable when the result is correct.
6/ If you wish to access this documentation from BCS, rename it BCS.doc

